        output="Based on the provided text, here are the key details regarding the xAI and X mergers and their accounting treatment:\n\n### Merger Dates\n*   **xAI Merger (SpaceX acquires xAI):** Effective **February 2, 2026**.\n*   **X Merger (xAI acquires X and X.AI Corp.):** Effective **March 28, 2025**.\n    *   X.AI Corp. began operations in March 2023, and Twitter (later X) was acquired by Elon Musk in October 2022.\n\n### Accounting Treatment: Common-Control Reorganization & Retrospective Combination\nThe mergers were accounted for as **reorganizations of entities under common control** because Elon Musk held a controlling financial interest (majority voting interest) in SpaceX, xAI, and X throughout the periods presented.\n\nAs a result, the following retrospective accounting principles were applied:\n1.  **Combined Historical Financials:** SpaceX's consolidated financial statements were prepared to reflect the **retrospective combination** of the net assets of SpaceX, xAI, and X for all historical periods presented.\n2.  **No New Goodwill or Intangibles:** No new goodwill or other intangible assets were recorded as part of the mergers.\n3.  **Elimination of Intercompany Transactions:** All historical related party transactions between the entities were eliminated in consolidation.\n4.  **Combined Equity:** The capital stock and shareholders’ equity for all periods presented reflect the continuation of the historical SpaceX capital stock and shareholders’ equity, combined with the historical capital stock and shareholders’ equity of X and xAI, adjusted for the merger exchange ratios.\n5.  **Change in Reporting Entity:** This treatment constitutes a **change in reporting entity**, meaning the financial statements for prior periods are presented as if the combined company (SpaceX, xAI, and X) had always existed.\n\n**Important Exception:** While common stock was retrospectively combined, **xAI's Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock** was *not* retrospectively recast for periods prior to the xAI Merger. It remained presented as a separate equity class of xAI until its conversion into SpaceX Common Stock occurred at the merger closing.\n\n### Key References in the Text\nThe explanation is consistently repeated across multiple sections (Notes to the Financial Statements, Preamble, Summary Data). For the definitive accounting policy, the text refers to **Note 1 (Nature of Business)** and the related **Note 12 or 13 (Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock and Shareholders’ Equity)**.",
